## 5. Pure-Logic Module Discipline

Modules under `model/`, `editor/`, `board/`, `game_sessions/`, and `resources/` must be
**framework-free**: no React imports, no DOM APIs, no `window`/`document` references.

These modules are imported directly by hooks and components. They must never import from
`react`, `react-dom`, or any browser-only API.

```typescript
// Good â€” pure-logic module
export const parsePgnToModel = (pgn: string): PgnModel => { ... };

// Bad â€” framework leak
import { useState } from "react";  // forbidden in model/
```

---

## 6. State and Service Access Patterns

### Reading state in components
Always use typed selectors from `src/state/selectors.ts`:

```tsx
const isOpen: boolean = selectIsMenuOpen(state);
const sessions: SessionItemState[] = selectSessions(state);
```

Never read fields from `state` directly by key in component bodies.

### Calling services in components
All side-effects and state mutations go through `useServiceContext()` callbacks:

```tsx
const services = useServiceContext();
<button onClick={() => services.setMenuOpen(false)}>Close</button>
```

Never call `dispatch` directly from a component for game/service logic.
`dispatch` is permitted only for pure UI-local state (e.g. toggling an editor panel open/closed)
that has no corresponding service abstraction.

### Controlled inputs
All form inputs driven by `AppStoreState` must be **controlled** (use `value`/`checked`, not
`defaultValue`/`defaultChecked`):

```tsx
<input
  type="range"
  value={moveDelayMs}
  onChange={(e: ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>): void => {
    services.setMoveDelayMs(Number(e.target.value));
  }}
/>
```

---

## 7. Internationalisation

All user-facing strings must be resolved through the translator:

```tsx
const t: (key: string, fallback?: string) => string = useTranslator();

// Good
<p>{t("menu.title", "Menu")}</p>
<button aria-label={t("menu.close", "Close menu")}>Ă—</button>

// Bad â€” hardcoded English
<p>Menu</p>
```

`aria-label`, `title`, `placeholder`, and button text are all user-facing and must use `t()`.

---

## 8. Architecture Constraints (do not violate)

- **Single state store**: All UI state lives in `AppStoreState` (`useReducer`). No local `useState`
  for state that needs to be shared across components.
- **Service initialisation**: All service singletons are created inside `useAppStartup`.
  Services are never constructed inside components.
- **ServiceContext**: The only channel for components to trigger service logic.
  Do not pass service callbacks as individual props; components call `useServiceContext()`.
- **No backend mediation for local resources**: Local file read/write stays in client code.
- **No SQL schema in frontend**: All DB schema/migrations live in `resource/database/`.
- **`bootstrap_shared.ts` is a shared contract file**: It must not be deleted or merged into
  frontend-only modules; pure-logic modules (`session_store`, `session_persistence`,
  `resources/index`) depend on it.
